All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
Add
The Add class handles adding new Flat objects to the storage.
Clear
The Clear class removes all elements from the storage.
CommandsList
The CommandsList class processes user commands and executes them accordingly.
ExecuteScript
The ExecuteScript class reads and executes commands from a file.
Exit
The Exit class terminates the program.
FilterByTransport
The FilterByTransport class filters flats by transport type.
FilterContainsName
The FilterContainsName class filters flats by a substring in their name.
Help
The Help class displays a list of available commands.
Info
The Info class displays information about the current collection.
Main
The Main class is the entry point of the application.
MinById
The MinById class finds and prints the flat with the smallest ID.
Reader
The Reader class is responsible for reading JSON files and parsing them into objects.
RemoveById
The RemoveById class removes a flat from storage by its ID.
RemoveFirst
The RemoveFirst class removes the first element from the storage.
Reorder
The Reorder class reverses the order of elements in the storage.
Save
The Save class writes the current storage collection to a file.
Show
The Show class displays all elements in the collection.
Sort
The Sort class sorts the storage of flats in alphabetical order by name.
Storage
The Storage class represents a storage system for Flat objects.
Update
The Update class updates the attributes of an existing flat in the storage.
Writer
The Writer class is responsible for writing objects to JSON files.
